rComments: I don't really understand how she marks.. Somehow I thought I was doing really well in the class, I got really great feedback and was always participating. Class and prof seemed to really be very passionate about my work. But then the marks came out and it's as if they weren't into it at all. I thought it was a mistake at first..but I confirmed it.
Very confusing... critiques went really well with excellent feedback. But then the marks were not consistent. Good critique did not mean good mark. Not great.

One of the best professors that I have ever had in my academic career.  She is experienced as a professor.  She possesses a vast knowledge of her subject.  And most importantly, she knows how to challenge and encourage her students to produce their best work. This what university should be like.
great prof! extremely open to different approaches to artmaking. A pleasure to talk to.
Wondeerful dDeoartment Chair, very helpful and insightful. I strongly suggest students read her book and take her classes.

The most easy teacher to follow in all my university studies. Was passionate and very knowledgable about what she taught. Very helpful and also gave an interesting class. I learnt a lot and retained most of what she taught which is rare for me.
